<name>DATA LIST / ACTIVE TEST</name>
<subpara id="RM0000010VM00PX_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___0000AA300000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<atten4>
<ptxt>By accessing the DATA LIST displayed on the intelligent tester, you can perform such functions as reading the values of switches and sensors without removing any parts. Reading the DATA LIST is the first step in troubleshooting is one method to save labor time.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<step1>
<ptxt>DATA LIST FOR OCCUPANT CLASSIFICATION ECU</ptxt>
<step2>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname="C131977E01" width="2.775699831in" height="2.775699831in"/>
</figure>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG).</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Turn the tester ON.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Enter the following menus: DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / OCCUPANT DETECT / DATA LIST.</ptxt>
</step2>
<step2>
<ptxt>Check the values by referring to the table below.</ptxt>
